ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: A1: One or more of SOPS items:  P1, P2, P3, P4, P5 scored 6  (If A1 is NO, then A2-A6 and A8 are NA and A7 = No)
A2: If A1 is YES, symptoms are not explained better by a DSM 5 disorder
A3: If A1 is YES, symptoms are not seriously dangerous or disorganizing
A4: If A1 is YES, does not meet DSM 5 criteria for psychotic disorders

A5: If A1 is YES, are the symptoms currently present for at least several minutes per day (not more than one hour) at least one time per month, up to an average frequency of several minutes per day four days per week over one month?
A6: If A1 is YES, did the symptoms begin or worsen to a 6 in the past three months?
A7: A1, A2, A3, A4, A5 and A6 are Yes rule in current BIPS criteria  (If A7 is YES, A9-A20 are all NA
A8: If A7 is YES, record date when current BIPS criteria began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
A9: If A7 is NO, was BIPS criteria diagnosed on the SIPS previously? (If A9 is NO, A10-A20 are all NA)
A10: Are A1 - A5 all YES?
A11: If A10 is YES, have symptoms lasted at a 6 longer than three months?
A12: If A10 and A11 are Yes rule in current BIPS persistence (If A12 is Yes, A14-A22 are all NA)
A13: If A12 is YES, record date when current BIPS persistence began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
A14: Is A9 YES?
A15: Is A1 NO and for 6 months or less?
A16: Are A1 to A4 YES but A5 is NO?
A17: If A14 and A15 OR A16 are Yes rule in current BIPS partial remission  (If A17 is YES, A20-A22 are all NA)
A18: If A14 and A17 are YES, record date when current BIPS partial remission began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
A19: Is A9 YES?
A20: Is A1 NO and for more than 6 months?
A21: If A19 and A20 are Yes rule in current BIPS full remission
A22: If A21 is YES, record date when current BIPS full remission began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
B1: One or more of SOPS items P1, P2, P3, P4, P5 scored 3-5  (If B1 is NO then B2-B4 and B6 are NA and B5 = No)
B2: If B1 is YES, the symptoms are NOT better accounted for by a DSM 5 disorder
B3: If B1 is YES, have the symptoms occurred at an average frequency of at least once per week in the past month?
B4: If B1 is YES, have the symptoms begun within the past year, or do any currently rate one or more scale points higher compared to 12 months ago?
B5: B1, B2, B3 and B4 are Yes rule in current APS criteria (If B5 is YES, B7-B18 are all NA)
B6: If B5 is YES, record date when current APS criteria began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
B7: If B5 is NO, was APS criteria diagnosed on the SIPS previously? (If B7 is NO, B8-B18 are all NA)
B8: Are B1 - B3 all YES?
B9: Is B4 NO?
B10: If B8 and B9 are Yes rule in current APS persistence (If B10 is YES, B12-B19 are all NA)
B11: If B10 is YES, record date when current APS persistence began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
B12: Is B7 YES?
B13: Is B1 NO and for 6 months or less?
B14: Are B1 and B2 YES but B3 is NO?
B15: If B12 and B13 OR B14 are Yes rule in current APS partial remission  (If B15 is YES, B17-B20 are all NA)
B16: If B15 is YES, record date when current APS partial remission began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
B17: Is B7 YES?
B18: Is B1 NO and for more than 6 months?
B19: If B17 and B18 is Yes rule in current APS full remission
B20: If B17 is YES, record date when current APS full remission began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
C1: The person has met criteria for Schizotypal Personality Disorder, now or in the past
C2: The person has a first degree relative with a psychotic disorder
C3: The person has experienced at least a 30% drop in GAF score compared to one year ago, sustained over the past month
C4: If C1 or C2 are Yes and C3 is Yes rule in current GRD criteria (If C4 is YES, C5-C14 are all NA)
C5: If C4 scored Yes, record date when current GRD criteria began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
C6: If C4 is NO, was GRD criteria diagnosed on the SIPS previously?  (If C6 is NO, C7-C14 are all NA)
C7: Is the persons GAF score lower than 90% of its baseline before decline?  (Baseline is determined by the GAF score 12 months prior to the date in C5)
C8: If C7 is Yes rule in current GRD persistence  (If C8 is YES, C10-C14 are all NA)
C9: If C8 is YES, record date when current GRD persistence began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
C10: Is C6 YES?
C11: Is the persons GAF score at least 90% of its baseline before decline and for 6 months or less? (If C11 is YES, C12-C14 are all NA)
C12: If C10 and C11 are YES, record date when current GRD partial remission began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
C13: Is C6 YES?
C14: Is the persons GAF score at least 90% of its baseline before decline and for more than 6 months?
C15: If C13 and C14 are Yes rule in current GRD full remission
C16: If C15 is yes, record date when current GRD full remission began: (MM/DD/YYYY)
Subject's Current Clinical State
Does the subject meet CAARMS conversion criteria?
Date met CAARMS conversion criteria:
Site
session ID/screening ID
Visit name
Subject Type
Data quality
Notes: 0=No data (cancelled); 1=Data entered but only once, has missing data; 2=Data entered but only once, no missing data; 3=Double entered; 4=Data frozen for cleaning; 5=Data clean/locked

ElementDescription: Checks for a pass/fail on Elig for Inclusion
Visit number
